<div id="review_1705221535" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1705221535" />
    <a title="Rebecka" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6476980-rebecka"><img alt="Rebecka" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1404195253p2/6476980.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1705221535?book_show_action=true">Jul 21, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rebecka" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rebecka" href="/user/show/6476980-rebecka">Rebecka</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9785170042258" href="/book/show/2191154._">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6476980-rebecka?shelf=books-i-own">books-i-own</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6476980-rebecka?shelf=soviet-related">soviet-related</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6476980-rebecka?shelf=read_in_russian">read_in_russian</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1705221535" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1559987499394226921">Finally, a Russian book that I REALLY liked! This is an extremely well written, slow paced story of the daily life of patients and employees at a cancer ward somewhere in an Asian Soviet republic in 1954, with the soviet mindset, customs, oppression and resignation, coupled with fear of death. Wonderfully interesting!<br/><br/></span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

